-- Solar Subsidies to Cost Further 18 Billion Euros, Spiegel Says
-- B y   A l e x   W e b b
-- 2012-01-14T16:58:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-14/solar-subsidies-to-cost-further-18-billion-euros-spiegel-says.html
German subsidies for solar panels
installed in the past year will cost consumers 18 billion euros
($23 billion) in 2012,  Spiegel  reported in a preview of an
article to be published tomorrow, citing a report by the Rhein-
Westfalen Institute for Economic Research.  This pushes the total level of funding commitments to
beyond 100 billion euros, the magazine said, citing the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
